WEBVTT

00:00:02.400 --> 00:00:06.990
That concludes my announcements for the day.

00:00:06.990 --> 00:00:09.300
One more thing before we get started.

00:00:09.300 --> 00:00:13.550
Dojima-san's procedure has been scheduled for today.

00:00:14.300 --> 00:00:20.180
He says, "Don't come checking up on me. Focus on your work!"

00:00:21.840 --> 00:00:25.880
- So, let's get to it.
- Yes, Ma'am.

00:00:25.880 --> 00:00:29.750
Team Leader Takachiho, there was one more thing on the docket.

00:00:29.750 --> 00:00:31.400
Right, I almost forgot.

00:00:31.400 --> 00:00:34.120
- Kaneshita.
- Yes?

00:00:34.120 --> 00:00:36.600
How do you feel about getting certified?

00:00:36.600 --> 00:00:38.780
- What?
- Certified,

00:00:38.780 --> 00:00:42.190
to eventually work for the SR squad.

00:00:42.190 --> 00:00:44.170
- The SRs?
- Those "Super Rangers"?

00:00:44.170 --> 00:00:46.870
Also known as the Yokohama Special Advanced Rescue Team?

00:00:46.870 --> 00:00:48.480
Yes. Isn't that right, Tanaka-kun?

00:00:48.480 --> 00:00:49.860
Indeed.

00:00:49.860 --> 00:00:52.080
A certain someone has recommended you.

00:00:52.080 --> 00:00:53.630
Me?

00:00:53.630 --> 00:00:56.200
Isn't that amazing?

00:00:56.200 --> 00:00:57.320
Right...

00:00:57.320 --> 00:01:00.350
It's only the squad every firefighter dreams of joining.

00:01:00.350 --> 00:01:01.800
That's right.

00:01:01.800 --> 00:01:05.030
While I'd love for you to stay as a dispatcher,

00:01:05.030 --> 00:01:09.040
it's ultimately your choice to make, Kaneshita.

00:01:09.040 --> 00:01:11.150
Give it some careful thought, okay?

00:01:11.150 --> 00:01:12.710
I will.

00:01:12.710 --> 00:01:15.860
Now then, let us get to work.

00:01:15.860 --> 00:01:18.830
- Yes, Ma'am.
- Yes, Ma'am.

00:01:28.910 --> 00:01:32.180
Fire department's 119. Is it a fire or medical emergency?

00:01:32.180 --> 00:01:37.320
Excuse me, but I tripped and hit my knee. It hurts so much; I can't walk...

00:01:37.320 --> 00:01:38.830
May I ask which leg?

00:01:38.830 --> 00:01:40.500
My left leg.

00:01:40.500 --> 00:01:43.550
It hurts so badly, and I can't feel my foot anymore.

00:01:43.550 --> 00:01:46.080
I got it. Please tell us where to send the ambulance.

00:01:46.080 --> 00:01:48.580
Oh, where am I?

00:01:48.580 --> 00:01:50.530
Check a telephone pole if possible.

00:01:50.530 --> 00:01:52.040
An address should be written there.

00:01:52.040 --> 00:01:57.860
It says 1-22-3 Midorigahama, Aoba Ward.

00:01:57.860 --> 00:02:01.770
- "1-22-3 Midorigahama, Aoba Ward"?
- Yes...

00:02:01.770 --> 00:02:03.900
And are you feeling pain anywhere else?

00:02:03.900 --> 00:02:06.710
No. Just my knee.

00:02:06.710 --> 00:02:08.230
Ouch... this really...
[Dispatch]

00:02:08.230 --> 00:02:12.090
Hang in there, Sir. I've sent an ambulance your way.

00:02:12.090 --> 00:02:15.460
Please stay calm; don't agitate your knee any further.

00:02:15.460 --> 00:02:18.140
Could I also get your name?

00:02:20.140 --> 00:02:24.020
Fire department's 119. Is it a fire or medical emergency?

00:02:24.020 --> 00:02:29.820
[119 Emergency Call]

00:02:29.820 --> 00:02:33.980
[CALL 9]

00:02:33.980 --> 00:02:35.570
Do you want to head back out there?

00:02:35.570 --> 00:02:38.300
Joining the SR was always your dream.

00:02:38.300 --> 00:02:40.560
I'll come to a decision myself.

00:02:40.560 --> 00:02:43.550
Th-There's been a landslide! My home has been ruined!

00:02:43.550 --> 00:02:45.510
Noharadai is my wife's hometown.

00:02:45.510 --> 00:02:47.140
She's visiting family there now.

00:02:47.140 --> 00:02:49.110
It seems another landslide has occurred.

00:02:49.110 --> 00:02:51.580
Hikari? Hikari, is that you?

00:02:53.890 --> 00:02:55.910
- The SR?
- Yes.

00:02:55.910 --> 00:02:57.750
My responsibilities would drastically change if I transfer.

00:02:57.750 --> 00:03:00.100
I'd be working out here again.

00:03:00.100 --> 00:03:03.180
They'd even send me overseas, if necessary.

00:03:03.180 --> 00:03:05.620
Yes, I had a feeling.

00:03:05.620 --> 00:03:07.340
Hikari, what do you think?

00:03:07.340 --> 00:03:11.030
Dad says he might join the SR.

00:03:12.970 --> 00:03:16.540
Well, Dad was cool as a dispatcher...

00:03:16.540 --> 00:03:18.910
- Wait, really?
- Yeah.

00:03:18.910 --> 00:03:20.930
But the SR is awesome, too.

00:03:20.930 --> 00:03:23.040
So which is it?

00:03:24.410 --> 00:03:26.970
It's an SR Blower System!

00:03:41.070 --> 00:03:43.480
Do you want to head back out there?

00:03:43.480 --> 00:03:44.840
Pardon?

00:03:44.840 --> 00:03:49.440
Joining the SR was always your dream.

00:03:49.440 --> 00:03:52.220
Well, I guess.

00:03:53.010 --> 00:03:54.680
I see.

00:04:03.060 --> 00:04:06.720
- Fire department's 119. Is it a fire or medical emergency?
- It's an accident!

00:04:06.720 --> 00:04:09.210
My car slipped up onto a pedestrian walkway,

00:04:09.210 --> 00:04:11.270
and I... I hit a person!

00:04:11.270 --> 00:04:14.120
Understood. Please tell us where to send the ambulance.

00:04:14.120 --> 00:04:18.950
Would the name of this intersection work?

00:04:18.950 --> 00:04:22.850
- Yes, go ahead.
- It's the intersection right before Koshimiya Station.

00:04:22.850 --> 00:04:25.160
Thank you.

00:04:25.160 --> 00:04:28.750
And is the individual who has been hit conscious?

00:04:28.750 --> 00:04:31.290
Yes, but they're crouching down.

00:04:31.290 --> 00:04:33.470
Fire department's 119. Is it a fire or medical emergency?

00:04:33.470 --> 00:04:36.090
- A medical emergency.
- What seems to be the issue?

00:04:36.090 --> 00:04:38.500
I'm out camping with my friends from university,

00:04:38.500 --> 00:04:40.390
and one is shivering like crazy in our tent.

00:04:40.390 --> 00:04:42.390
Maybe it's the cold weather...

00:04:42.390 --> 00:04:43.660
Which campground are you at?

00:04:43.660 --> 00:04:46.690
Aoyagi Campground, in Seya Ward.

00:04:46.690 --> 00:04:47.920
Do they feel feverish?

00:04:47.920 --> 00:04:50.780
No, I don't think so.

00:04:50.780 --> 00:04:52.140
I see.

00:04:52.140 --> 00:04:54.870
Fire department's 119. Is it a fire or medical emergency?

00:04:54.870 --> 00:04:59.470
Hello. I think I've caught some sort of stomach bug.

00:04:59.470 --> 00:05:05.120
I've been throwing up and feeling nauseous as well.

00:05:05.120 --> 00:05:08.490
Got it. Could you please tell us where you are?

00:05:08.490 --> 00:05:11.290
Yes, 2-10-8 Koshibadai, Asahi Ward.

00:05:11.290 --> 00:05:14.680
My name is Numata.

00:05:14.680 --> 00:05:18.300
So 2-10-8 Koshibadai, Asahi Ward.

00:05:18.300 --> 00:05:19.690
- Numata-san, right?
- Yes.

00:05:19.690 --> 00:05:22.330
And is that your home, Ma'am?

00:05:22.330 --> 00:05:23.390
Yes.

00:05:23.390 --> 00:05:27.570
I've sent an ambulance your way. Please tell me more about your symptoms.

00:05:27.570 --> 00:05:28.790
Do you feel feverish?

00:05:28.790 --> 00:05:34.430
I'm not too certain. I feel a bit out of it.

00:05:34.430 --> 00:05:38.280
Have I caught the norovirus after all?

00:05:38.280 --> 00:05:40.440
Very sorry, but we can't give diagnoses ourselves.

00:05:40.440 --> 00:05:43.100
Try asking what she ate yesterday or the day before.

00:05:43.100 --> 00:05:47.640
Have you eaten anything in the last couple days that could be the cause?

00:05:47.640 --> 00:05:52.140
Well, I did go camping with my friends two days ago.

00:05:52.140 --> 00:05:55.460
We enjoyed some grilled oysters together.

00:05:55.460 --> 00:05:58.440
Perhaps that was it.

00:05:59.200 --> 00:06:00.850
And which campground did you stay at?

00:06:00.850 --> 00:06:05.170
We went to the Aoyagi Campground in Seya Ward.

00:06:05.170 --> 00:06:08.310
- "Aoyagi Campground in Seya Ward"?
- Yes.

00:06:08.310 --> 00:06:10.860
That's the same campground.

00:06:10.860 --> 00:06:13.920
Uesugi-kun, ask what they ate. They might have norovirus as well.

00:06:13.920 --> 00:06:16.620
Did you all eat anything at the campground?

00:06:16.620 --> 00:06:19.070
Yes. We were grilling oysters just earlier.

00:06:19.070 --> 00:06:21.270
- You all ate oysters?
- Yes.

00:06:21.270 --> 00:06:22.920
And how long ago was that?

00:06:22.920 --> 00:06:26.350
About 30-40 minutes ago.

00:06:26.350 --> 00:06:28.810
That's too fast for norovirus to show symptoms.

00:06:28.810 --> 00:06:30.430
Ask about other symptoms.

00:06:30.430 --> 00:06:34.070
- Does your friend have other symptoms?
- Please contact the police after our call.

00:06:34.070 --> 00:06:36.460
- Okay.
- The ambulance will arrive shortly.

00:06:36.460 --> 00:06:38.600
- Stay in the vicinity for their arrival.
- Right.

00:06:38.600 --> 00:06:41.650
Ask about her car's condition before you end the call.

00:06:41.650 --> 00:06:44.210
Ma'am, what condition is your car in?

00:06:44.210 --> 00:06:47.480
Has it hit anything?

00:06:47.480 --> 00:06:50.600
It hit a telephone pole. The front has been squashed.

00:06:50.600 --> 00:06:52.590
Is it significantly crushed?

00:06:52.590 --> 00:06:56.340
Do you see any smoke or leaking liquids perhaps?

00:06:56.340 --> 00:07:00.270
Yes, I see something leaking. Maybe oil?

00:07:00.270 --> 00:07:02.710
- So there is a leak?
- Yes.

00:07:02.710 --> 00:07:04.700
Ma'am, please step away from your vehicle now.

00:07:04.700 --> 00:07:06.210
R-Right.
[Emergency]

00:07:06.210 --> 00:07:08.970
They say their face and lips feel numb?

00:07:08.970 --> 00:07:10.710
Yes, face and lips.

00:07:10.710 --> 00:07:14.180
Numbness 30 to 40 minutes after eating oysters?

00:07:14.180 --> 00:07:17.440
That paralysis could be due to shellfish poisoning.

00:07:17.440 --> 00:07:19.410
"Shellfish poisoning"?

00:07:19.410 --> 00:07:22.000
Uesugi-kun, they may be suffering from shellfish poisoning.

00:07:22.000 --> 00:07:24.060
Ask if they're breathing.

00:07:24.060 --> 00:07:27.370
Is that numbness only in their face? Are they able to breath?

00:07:27.370 --> 00:07:31.340
How are you feeling? Can you breath?

00:07:33.440 --> 00:07:36.760
Okay, they say it's getting harder to breath.

00:07:36.760 --> 00:07:39.170
Understood. An ambulance is already on its way.

00:07:39.170 --> 00:07:42.660
- Please call 119 again if they get worse.
- I will.

00:07:42.660 --> 00:07:46.440
Yamashitacho paramedics, this is Yokohama Fire Bureau.

00:07:46.440 --> 00:07:51.910
I'm sending the Central rescue team to assist. There may have been a gas leak.

00:07:55.170 --> 00:07:58.120
[Iida]

00:07:58.120 --> 00:08:00.740
- Yes?
- Hey. Do you have time now?

00:08:00.740 --> 00:08:01.780
Sure.

00:08:01.780 --> 00:08:04.760
We were able to clean up Koshimiya Station without a hassle.

00:08:04.760 --> 00:08:08.250
Some quick-witted dispatcher spoke up before a fire erupted.

00:08:08.250 --> 00:08:09.800
That was you, wasn't it?

00:08:09.800 --> 00:08:12.710
We would've sent you even if I weren't there.

00:08:13.460 --> 00:08:15.830
It seems you're really shaping up as a dispatcher.

00:08:15.830 --> 00:08:18.460
Have you lost all interest in working out here?

00:08:19.670 --> 00:08:22.820
I know SR sent you an offer.

00:08:22.820 --> 00:08:25.590
I knew you had a hand in this.

00:08:25.590 --> 00:08:28.550
You always wanted to join the SR squad.

00:08:28.550 --> 00:08:33.410
Either way, I look forward to working with you again out here.

00:08:43.110 --> 00:08:46.860
Fire department's 119. Is it a fire or medical emergency?

00:08:46.860 --> 00:08:51.600
Well, I fell with my bike.

00:08:51.600 --> 00:08:54.380
Fell? Where are you now, Sir?

00:08:54.380 --> 00:08:58.590
Oh, great question. I can see only the sky.

00:08:58.590 --> 00:09:00.310
"The sky"?

00:09:00.310 --> 00:09:04.550
How far did you fall? Are you unable to move?

00:09:04.550 --> 00:09:07.560
Yes. I can't move an inch.

00:09:07.560 --> 00:09:11.680
It's freezing out here, and I have no idea where I am.

00:09:11.680 --> 00:09:14.720
Got it. Could I get your name, Sir?

00:09:14.720 --> 00:09:16.610
It's Kusaka.

00:09:16.610 --> 00:09:18.280
Kusaka-san, right?

00:09:18.280 --> 00:09:21.460
Where were you biking before you fell?

00:09:21.460 --> 00:09:25.540
I was on the road I always take back home, so that's...

00:09:25.540 --> 00:09:33.090
just before District 2 of Kasaicho, in Hodogaya Ward.

00:09:33.090 --> 00:09:37.510
- So, you are around District 2 of Kasaicho, Hodogaya Ward.
- Yes.

00:09:37.510 --> 00:09:42.100
I've sent an ambulance your way. Are you hurt anywhere?

00:09:42.100 --> 00:09:44.240
Perhaps you hit yourself when you fell?

00:09:44.240 --> 00:09:47.320
Great question. I'm not too sure.

00:09:47.320 --> 00:09:48.570
[Irrigation channel]

00:09:48.570 --> 00:09:54.320
Kaneshita-san, he may have fallen into an irrigation channel.

00:09:54.320 --> 00:09:57.750
Kusaka-san, do you have the capacity to yell?

00:09:57.750 --> 00:10:00.520
If so, please try calling for help.

00:10:00.520 --> 00:10:03.760
Someone may walk by and notice you.

00:10:03.760 --> 00:10:09.230
I'll try. Hello?

00:10:09.230 --> 00:10:11.280
Hello?

00:10:11.280 --> 00:10:15.230
- Please, please help me!
- Keep that up, Sir.

00:10:15.230 --> 00:10:16.680
Sure.

00:10:16.680 --> 00:10:19.990
- Hello? Anyone?
- Squads, this is Yokohama Fire Bureau.

00:10:19.990 --> 00:10:23.130
The injured man may have fallen into an irrigation channel.

00:10:23.130 --> 00:10:26.420
We believe he is somewhere along the Hodogaya-Asahi Road,

00:10:26.420 --> 00:10:28.690
within District 2 of Kasaicho.

00:10:28.690 --> 00:10:31.430
- Please focus your search there.
- Second Asahi fire squad. Copy that.

00:10:31.430 --> 00:10:33.780
It's so cold out here.

00:10:33.780 --> 00:10:37.850
Damn. Why me?

00:10:37.850 --> 00:10:41.280
- Sir, an ambulance will be there soon.
- Sure.

00:10:43.050 --> 00:10:46.660
It's currently raining in that area, isn't it?

00:10:46.660 --> 00:10:51.120
Kusaka-san. How long has it been since you fell?

00:10:51.120 --> 00:10:55.210
How long? I wonder.

00:10:55.890 --> 00:10:59.970
It seems I passed out at some point.

00:10:59.970 --> 00:11:01.730
I knew it.

00:11:01.730 --> 00:11:05.210
If he was in the rain for long, he may be suffering from hypothermia.

00:11:05.210 --> 00:11:10.160
I'm sure it must be freezing, Kusaka-san. Please hold on a bit longer.

00:11:12.060 --> 00:11:14.500
I'm absolutely drenched.

00:11:15.430 --> 00:11:19.490
Shoot, are my drafts soaked, too?

00:11:19.490 --> 00:11:22.800
You may stay on the line with us until the ambulance arrives.

00:11:22.800 --> 00:11:26.390
It's cold... Way too cold.

00:11:26.390 --> 00:11:30.990
Am I going to die out here?

00:11:30.990 --> 00:11:35.240
- Am I going to die?
- Hang in there. The ambulance has almost arrived.

00:11:35.240 --> 00:11:41.390
I haven't even won a single award for my manga yet.

00:11:41.390 --> 00:11:45.490
I don't want to die. Please, help me...

00:11:45.490 --> 00:11:47.490
Sir, you'll be okay. Hang in there.

00:11:47.490 --> 00:11:49.560
Help is almost there.

00:11:49.560 --> 00:11:53.300
- You can stay on the line with us until then.
- Please, help me.

00:11:53.300 --> 00:11:54.640
Hang in there.

00:11:54.640 --> 00:11:57.420
Kusaka-san, you can do it!

00:12:02.000 --> 00:12:04.400
- Hello there.
- Hey.

00:12:05.940 --> 00:12:09.030
I'm glad that man with the bike turned out to be okay.

00:12:09.030 --> 00:12:10.520
Right.

00:12:13.540 --> 00:12:15.380
Thanks.

00:12:16.280 --> 00:12:17.470
What?

00:12:17.470 --> 00:12:20.710
For earlier. I appreciated the help.

00:12:21.980 --> 00:12:23.780
Excuse me?

00:12:23.780 --> 00:12:25.840
What?

00:12:25.840 --> 00:12:27.680
No, it's just...

00:12:28.550 --> 00:12:30.940
This really isn't like you.

00:12:31.900 --> 00:12:34.770
You've never thanked me for anything before.

00:12:38.960 --> 00:12:42.270
- Say, Kaneshita-san.
- What now?

00:12:42.920 --> 00:12:45.230
Don't you want to join the SR?

00:12:45.230 --> 00:12:46.890
You want me to go?

00:12:46.890 --> 00:12:50.080
I just hope we rookies aren't keeping you here

00:12:50.080 --> 00:12:51.510
out of worry for us...

00:12:51.510 --> 00:12:54.050
You're giving yourselves too much credit.

00:12:54.050 --> 00:12:56.630
And I'm not worried, not in the slightest.

00:12:56.630 --> 00:13:00.630
Then why? I thought you wouldn't hesitate when given the offer.

00:13:00.630 --> 00:13:02.970
You want me to leave that badly?

00:13:02.970 --> 00:13:06.120
Like I said, that's not my point.

00:13:28.740 --> 00:13:31.200
How are you feeling, Sir?

00:13:33.660 --> 00:13:36.150
Right, sorry.

00:13:48.730 --> 00:13:50.320
Here.

00:14:09.750 --> 00:14:12.070
[What are you doing here?]

00:14:13.220 --> 00:14:18.510
You never said not to visit for advice.

00:14:18.510 --> 00:14:20.280
Sorry.

00:14:23.640 --> 00:14:29.130
I'm... being offered a spot on the SR squad.

00:14:29.990 --> 00:14:32.640
But I'm at a loss.

00:14:32.640 --> 00:14:36.410
It was always my dream to join SR, and yet...

00:14:38.960 --> 00:14:46.160
When I was a firefighter, I once brought great harm to a junior of mine.

00:14:46.160 --> 00:14:48.960
- Kaneshita-san?
- Stay back!

00:14:49.630 --> 00:14:52.140
Shiomi! Shiomi!

00:14:52.140 --> 00:14:54.030
Shiomi!

00:14:54.890 --> 00:14:58.520
I ended up disrupting his life.

00:15:01.860 --> 00:15:05.980
That incident is the reason I came to the Command department.

00:15:07.610 --> 00:15:11.790
My wife is also anxious seeing me consider going back out there.

00:15:11.790 --> 00:15:13.850
Of course, I understand her perspective.

00:15:13.850 --> 00:15:19.310
My wife did seem a bit relieved when I transferred to Command.

00:15:20.890 --> 00:15:25.040
Being a dispatcher also gives me a great sense of accomplishment.

00:15:26.450 --> 00:15:33.040
Dispatchers are always the first to prevent a disaster.

00:15:35.880 --> 00:15:40.500
Still, when I hear those voices crying for help,

00:15:40.500 --> 00:15:45.440
I feel that urge to be there, and...

00:16:03.140 --> 00:16:06.900
[So you'd go to SR if I gave the word?]

00:16:13.180 --> 00:16:15.730
Sorry, you're right, Sir.

00:16:15.730 --> 00:16:18.530
I'll come to a decision myself.

00:16:21.890 --> 00:16:24.050
And before I forget...

00:16:24.050 --> 00:16:28.310
Everyone paid their "Legend" fines before I came here.

00:16:28.310 --> 00:16:32.940
You've got about 60 coins in there. Ten times per person.

00:16:32.940 --> 00:16:34.550
And another for the one I just said.

00:16:34.550 --> 00:16:35.660
[1 "Legend" = 100 Yen]

00:16:41.640 --> 00:16:42.600
[Chinese Restaurant]

00:16:42.600 --> 00:16:45.250
Nice restaurant! Maybe I'll invite the guys from Central Station here, too.

00:16:45.250 --> 00:16:47.750
Don't. It'd get way too stifling.

00:16:47.750 --> 00:16:49.620
Right.

00:16:49.620 --> 00:16:53.310
- Is your exam the day after tomorrow, Niijima-san?
- Yes.

00:16:53.310 --> 00:16:56.140
The paramedic certification exam?

00:16:56.140 --> 00:16:57.930
Good luck.

00:16:58.730 --> 00:17:00.650
Sorry I took the day off.

00:17:00.650 --> 00:17:04.090
Don't apologize. I'd never say no if it were for a certification.

00:17:04.090 --> 00:17:05.140
Thank you.

00:17:05.140 --> 00:17:08.510
Niijima-san really is the personification of ambition.

00:17:08.510 --> 00:17:10.260
I should learn a thing or two from her.

00:17:10.260 --> 00:17:13.290
Maybe I should go get certifications, too.

00:17:13.290 --> 00:17:15.050
You have ambitions? That's news to me.

00:17:15.050 --> 00:17:18.750
- Uesugi-kun, do you realize how—
- Excuse me, another lemon sour, please.

00:17:18.750 --> 00:17:21.570
- I was still talking.
- I'm going to the restroom.

00:17:21.570 --> 00:17:25.090
- Okay, we'll continue this conversation there.
- Don't follow me!

00:17:25.090 --> 00:17:28.550
And don't cut off your Senpai when he's talking to you!

00:17:28.550 --> 00:17:30.020
Hey!

00:17:31.640 --> 00:17:34.020
- I'll join you two next Monday.
- Sounds good.

00:17:34.020 --> 00:17:36.440
- Grandpa is getting us sushi today.
- Really?

00:17:36.440 --> 00:17:38.260
Eat your fill of salted salmon roe.

00:17:38.260 --> 00:17:41.040
- Greet your parents for me.
- Sure. See you later.

00:17:41.040 --> 00:17:44.310
- Take care. See you soon.
- Bye!

00:17:58.030 --> 00:18:00.320
Fire department's 119. Is it a fire or medical emergency?

00:18:00.320 --> 00:18:03.070
I have a major roof leak.

00:18:03.070 --> 00:18:06.200
- "A roof leak."
- Yes, it's dripping everywhere.

00:18:06.200 --> 00:18:08.050
Can you do something about this?

00:18:08.050 --> 00:18:11.460
I'm sorry, but we don't accept such inquiries.

00:18:11.460 --> 00:18:15.130
- I'd suggest contacting a local repair company instead.
- Really?

00:18:15.130 --> 00:18:17.470
This is an emergency line. I will end our call now.

00:18:17.470 --> 00:18:19.170
A leak is an emergency.

00:18:19.170 --> 00:18:21.540
Sorry for the inconvenience, Sir. Have a good one.

00:18:21.540 --> 00:18:22.960
Everyone's calling for leaks.

00:18:22.960 --> 00:18:25.590
It's been a rainy week.

00:18:25.590 --> 00:18:29.630
Personally, I'm enjoying this peace.

00:18:32.630 --> 00:18:34.920
Fire department's 119. Is it a fire or medical emergency?

00:18:34.920 --> 00:18:38.080
Th-There's been a landslide!

00:18:38.080 --> 00:18:40.310
My home has been ruined!
[Emergency]

00:18:40.310 --> 00:18:42.860
Are you currently inside your home? Are you safe?

00:18:42.860 --> 00:18:48.210
I'm outside. And I'm fine, but my mother was still inside!
[Landslide]

00:18:48.210 --> 00:18:50.130
Your mother is still inside, right?

00:18:50.130 --> 00:18:52.090
- Could I get your address, Sir?
- R-Right.

00:18:52.090 --> 00:18:56.530
It's 1-309-4 Noharadai, Kanazawa Ward. The name's Murashige.

00:18:56.530 --> 00:19:01.510
You said, "1-309-4 Noharadai, Kanazawa Ward," Murashige-san?

00:19:01.510 --> 00:19:03.400
Yes.

00:19:03.400 --> 00:19:07.050
Murashige-san, I've sent a rescue squad your way.
[Dispatch]

00:19:07.050 --> 00:19:11.270
Do you know where your mother is within the debris?

00:19:12.180 --> 00:19:14.020
- Fire department's 119. Is it a fire or medical emergency?
- There's been a landslide.

00:19:14.020 --> 00:19:15.930
- Fire department's 119. Is it a fire or medical emergency?
- There's been a landslide.

00:19:15.930 --> 00:19:17.560
My neighbor's place was swept under.

00:19:17.560 --> 00:19:18.910
I see.

00:19:18.910 --> 00:19:22.730
Could I get that resident's address? And are you safe, Sir?

00:19:22.730 --> 00:19:26.500
Yes, I'm safe. We're in District 1 of Noharadai in Kanazawa Ward.

00:19:26.500 --> 00:19:28.320
My neighbors are the Murashiges.

00:19:28.320 --> 00:19:32.130
- "Murashige-san, District 1 Noharadai, Kanazawa Ward"?
- That's right.

00:19:32.130 --> 00:19:33.810
Were any other homes or individuals caught

00:19:33.810 --> 00:19:37.050
- in the debris?
- Fire department's 119. Is it a fire or medical emergency?

00:19:37.050 --> 00:19:41.460
Well, I heard the loudest noise outside just now.

00:19:41.460 --> 00:19:45.230
- Ma'am, where are you calling from?
- My home.

00:19:45.230 --> 00:19:49.140
I think there may have been a landslide in the town over.

00:19:49.140 --> 00:19:51.050
Could I get your address please?

00:19:51.050 --> 00:19:54.290
It's 3-106-5 Shiura, Kanazawa Ward.

00:19:54.290 --> 00:19:58.750
- My number is...
- We see your number here, Ma'am.

00:19:59.940 --> 00:20:01.410
- Team Leader.
- What is it?

00:20:01.410 --> 00:20:05.860
Noharadai is my wife's hometown; she's visiting family there now.

00:20:05.860 --> 00:20:09.020
Okay. Go contact them.

00:20:09.020 --> 00:20:11.010
Thank you.

00:20:12.700 --> 00:20:14.910
I can hear someone's voice from the back door!

00:20:14.910 --> 00:20:18.450
- From the back door, you say?
- Yes!

00:20:18.450 --> 00:20:20.090
Mom!

00:20:20.090 --> 00:20:22.840
Murashige-san, I need you to stand back and remain safe

00:20:22.840 --> 00:20:25.970
- until the rescue squad arrives.
- B-But...

00:20:25.970 --> 00:20:28.040
Get our cameras to show the Noharadai area.

00:20:28.040 --> 00:20:29.340
All right.

00:20:33.390 --> 00:20:34.390
I see it.

00:20:34.390 --> 00:20:37.220
Do landslides usually occur without any warning?

00:20:37.220 --> 00:20:39.460
This week of rain must have loosened the soil.

00:20:39.460 --> 00:20:41.220
This is Takachiho from Squad 3 speaking.
[Internal Call]

00:20:41.220 --> 00:20:43.830
There's been a landslide in the Kanazawa Ward.

00:20:43.830 --> 00:20:47.770
We'll have calls coming in. Be on stand-by.

00:20:47.770 --> 00:20:50.720
I see. So your place is safe?

00:20:50.720 --> 00:20:54.260
Yes. I think District 3 will be fine.

00:20:54.260 --> 00:20:59.140
But Mom and Dad went out to get us sushi.

00:20:59.140 --> 00:21:02.750
Just stay alert, okay? Evacuate as soon as you sense something wrong.

00:21:02.750 --> 00:21:06.220
We will. Did you want to talk to Hikari?

00:21:06.220 --> 00:21:07.820
Sure.

00:21:07.820 --> 00:21:09.720
Hikari, it's Dad.

00:21:12.590 --> 00:21:15.140
- Dad?
- Hikari,

00:21:15.140 --> 00:21:19.250
keep your mother safe until Grandma and Grandpa return, okay?

00:21:19.250 --> 00:21:20.600
I will.

00:21:20.600 --> 00:21:22.420
Good.

00:21:22.420 --> 00:21:24.360
Hey, it's me again.

00:21:24.360 --> 00:21:26.450
Mutsu-kun, are you okay?

00:21:26.450 --> 00:21:28.630
Yes, I'm fine.

00:21:29.410 --> 00:21:31.270
I see.

00:21:32.230 --> 00:21:35.730
Say, remember what we discussed the other day,

00:21:37.000 --> 00:21:39.380
about your possible transfer and all that?

00:21:39.380 --> 00:21:44.660
I gave it some thought on my own, and... well...

00:21:46.950 --> 00:21:48.860
Never mind.

00:21:48.860 --> 00:21:51.270
Let's talk about this later.

00:21:53.500 --> 00:21:56.630
Sorry to bother when you're busy. Thanks for calling.

00:21:56.630 --> 00:21:59.020
I'll talk to you later, okay?

00:21:59.020 --> 00:22:00.460
All right.

00:22:03.760 --> 00:22:07.360
A landslide in the Kanazawa Ward? Yes.

00:22:07.360 --> 00:22:10.390
- City Hall will announce evacuation protocols.
- How are they?

00:22:10.390 --> 00:22:12.360
My wife and son are safe at her parents' place.

00:22:12.360 --> 00:22:14.760
I've told them to evacuate if they need to.

00:22:14.760 --> 00:22:16.810
Go get them. We'll be fine.

00:22:16.810 --> 00:22:19.120
No, there will be more calls coming in.

00:22:19.120 --> 00:22:21.180
I'm returning to my station.

00:22:23.000 --> 00:22:26.070
- Kaneshita-san...
- Keep your eyes on your monitor.

00:22:26.070 --> 00:22:27.710
Okay.

00:22:28.970 --> 00:22:29.950
[Calls in Progress]

00:22:29.950 --> 00:22:31.800
[Radio - Firefighting Squad 6]

00:22:31.800 --> 00:22:34.220
Yokohama Fire, this is the Central Rescue Squad leader.

00:22:34.220 --> 00:22:35.860
What's your status, Captain?

00:22:35.860 --> 00:22:37.840
We've arrived at the collapsed house in District 1 of Noharadai.

00:22:37.840 --> 00:22:39.960
Now commencing rescue.

00:22:39.960 --> 00:22:43.100
Yokohama Fire, copy that. Transfer from radio to phone line.

00:22:43.100 --> 00:22:46.020
This is Central Rescue Squad leader; we'll make the call.

00:22:46.020 --> 00:22:48.020
[Internal Call]
[Accept Call]

00:22:48.020 --> 00:22:49.350
This is Command Team Leader Takachiho.

00:22:49.350 --> 00:22:51.460
This is Iida, Captain of Central Rescue Squad.

00:22:51.460 --> 00:22:54.020
The home has been partially destroyed by debris.

00:22:54.020 --> 00:23:00.290
We will proceed to rescue the individual reported to be by the back door.

00:23:00.290 --> 00:23:02.190
Sounds good, Captain.

00:23:06.550 --> 00:23:08.270
Captain Iida?

00:23:08.270 --> 00:23:09.800
Captain Iida!

00:23:09.800 --> 00:23:11.290
Are you all right?

00:23:11.290 --> 00:23:13.130
Sir? What happened?

00:23:13.130 --> 00:23:15.420
Someone get eyes on the situation!

00:23:15.420 --> 00:23:17.830
- What happened?
- We don't know, Sir.

00:23:17.830 --> 00:23:20.220
It seems another landslide has occurred!

00:23:20.220 --> 00:23:21.670
Do you know which area has been affected?

00:23:21.670 --> 00:23:24.510
Negative. We can't determine that from here!

00:23:29.200 --> 00:23:32.310
It's a distance from the first landslide.

00:23:33.130 --> 00:23:35.590
Fire department's 119. Is it a fire or medical emergency?

00:23:35.590 --> 00:23:38.400
Th-There's been a landslide and my home...

00:23:38.400 --> 00:23:40.810
My home has been destroyed!

00:23:40.810 --> 00:23:42.300
Sir, could I get your address?

00:23:42.300 --> 00:23:44.340
And are you currently safe?

00:23:44.340 --> 00:23:50.030
I was outside, but my house is gone. What do I do?

00:23:50.030 --> 00:23:51.630
Can you tell me your home's address, Sir?

00:23:51.630 --> 00:23:53.620
Oh, jeez...

00:23:53.620 --> 00:23:56.390
It was 3-216-3 Noharadai.

00:23:56.390 --> 00:23:58.470
District 3?

00:24:00.250 --> 00:24:03.930
It's 3-216-3 Noharadai?

00:24:03.930 --> 00:24:06.260
Were any other individuals or homes caught in the debris?

00:24:06.260 --> 00:24:07.900
Get SR on the case.

00:24:07.900 --> 00:24:09.970
Yes, Ma'am.

00:24:09.970 --> 00:24:11.500
This is Yogo from Command.

00:24:11.500 --> 00:24:14.410
A landslide has occurred in Noharadai, Kanazawa Ward.

00:24:14.410 --> 00:24:16.250
Requesting SR assistance.

00:24:16.250 --> 00:24:17.900
[Dispatch]

00:24:19.190 --> 00:24:22.030
Central Rescue Squad Captain, this is Yokohama Fire Bureau.

00:24:22.030 --> 00:24:26.220
I've sent a second squad to handle the other landslide.

00:24:26.220 --> 00:24:32.750
Copy that. Central will continue to rescue the trapped person in District 1.

00:24:32.750 --> 00:24:35.140
Please do.

00:24:46.630 --> 00:24:48.540
A rescue squad is headed your way.

00:24:48.540 --> 00:24:50.250
Please evacuate to a safe location.

00:24:50.250 --> 00:24:51.890
Where would that be?

00:24:51.890 --> 00:24:53.990
Is anywhere safe?

00:24:53.990 --> 00:24:56.370
For now, please keep your distance from the cliff.

00:24:56.370 --> 00:25:00.260
Fire department's 119. Is it a fire or medical emergency?

00:25:00.260 --> 00:25:02.930
You know how there were two landslides, right?

00:25:02.930 --> 00:25:07.160
Well, during that second one, a rock hit my leg really hard.

00:25:07.160 --> 00:25:10.690
I see. And where are you now, Sir?

00:25:10.690 --> 00:25:14.360
- Fire department's 119. Is it a fire or medical emergency?
- Finally!

00:25:14.360 --> 00:25:16.580
Is this 119?

00:25:16.580 --> 00:25:19.130
Yes, this is the 119 emergency line.

00:25:19.130 --> 00:25:23.730
My house collapsed, and I can't get out anymore!

00:25:23.730 --> 00:25:25.100
Could I get your address, Sir?

00:25:25.100 --> 00:25:33.000
I believe I'm 3-276-1 Noharadai, Kanazawa Ward.

00:25:33.000 --> 00:25:37.340
Okay, "3-276-1 Noharadai, Kanazawa Ward."

00:25:37.340 --> 00:25:39.520
- And you're inside your home?
- Yes.

00:25:39.520 --> 00:25:43.830
I fell over, and now my door doesn't seem to open.

00:25:43.830 --> 00:25:46.370
Are you hurt, Sir?

00:25:46.370 --> 00:25:49.420
I think something happened to my left elbow.

00:25:49.420 --> 00:25:51.590
Your left elbow...

00:25:52.730 --> 00:25:54.850
Fire department's 119. Is it a fire or medical emergency?

00:25:54.850 --> 00:25:58.120
- Did you hear about that landslide?
- Yes, Sir.

00:25:58.120 --> 00:26:00.300
Do you think us folk in Sakai will be fine?

00:26:00.300 --> 00:26:03.520
Our ward is also next to a mountain.

00:26:03.520 --> 00:26:04.910
What is your address, Sir?

00:26:04.910 --> 00:26:09.480
It's 3056 Sasanodai, Sakae Ward.

00:26:09.480 --> 00:26:14.200
It seems no evacuation has been ordered for your area.
[Disaster Live Updates]

00:26:15.060 --> 00:26:17.510
Fire department's 119. Is it a fire or medical emergency?

00:26:17.510 --> 00:26:22.370
Hello, I lead the neighborhood association in District 3 of Noharadai.

00:26:22.370 --> 00:26:25.170
The name's Hatakeyama.

00:26:25.170 --> 00:26:26.860
What seems to be the matter, Sir?

00:26:26.860 --> 00:26:33.490
Several homes in the district have been hit by a landslide.

00:26:33.490 --> 00:26:36.350
Have you evacuated to somewhere safe?

00:26:36.350 --> 00:26:37.790
Are you unharmed?

00:26:37.790 --> 00:26:42.100
Yes. We're currently visiting homes in the district,

00:26:42.100 --> 00:26:45.300
and we're evacuating people to the local community center.

00:26:45.300 --> 00:26:48.020
Hatakeyama-san, what are you doing? Hurry up!

00:26:48.020 --> 00:26:50.110
We have to stop by the Kimoto's place next!

00:26:50.110 --> 00:26:51.310
Yes, I hear you.

00:26:51.310 --> 00:26:53.780
I'll be right there.

00:26:56.940 --> 00:26:59.840
Kaneshita, were you able to contact your family?

00:26:59.840 --> 00:27:00.990
No.

00:27:00.990 --> 00:27:03.230
Go. We'll handle things here.

00:27:03.230 --> 00:27:05.400
We've already sent out the SR.

00:27:05.400 --> 00:27:07.840
My presence there will only hinder their work.

00:27:07.840 --> 00:27:10.070
- Still...
- All I can do now...

00:27:10.070 --> 00:27:14.420
is receive as many inquiries as possible from people in need

00:27:14.420 --> 00:27:18.040
and pass that information to rescue squads before they arrive.

00:27:20.110 --> 00:27:22.000
So, please.

00:27:29.390 --> 00:27:31.230
Fine.

00:27:31.230 --> 00:27:34.620
But if something happens, report to me immediately.

00:27:34.620 --> 00:27:36.280
Yes, Ma'am.

00:27:37.200 --> 00:27:41.960
Fire department's 119. Is it a fire or medical... Yes.

00:27:41.960 --> 00:27:44.560
You are Hatakeyama-san of the neighborhood association?

00:27:44.560 --> 00:27:46.550
- Yes.
- Hatakeyama-san?

00:27:46.550 --> 00:27:48.650
I'll take that call.

00:27:49.500 --> 00:27:51.900
The call has been transferred. Hatakeyama-san, is that you?

00:27:51.900 --> 00:27:53.880
Yes. I'm sorry for hanging up earlier.

00:27:53.880 --> 00:27:59.080
I had hoped to report the homes that were hit by the landslide.

00:27:59.080 --> 00:28:01.190
We appreciate your assistance, Sir.

00:28:02.050 --> 00:28:04.640
Fire department's 119. Is it a fire or medical emergency?

00:28:04.640 --> 00:28:07.300
- You know how there were those landslides?
- Yes.

00:28:07.300 --> 00:28:09.300
I actually live close by there.

00:28:09.300 --> 00:28:11.240
Should I be evacuating?

00:28:11.240 --> 00:28:14.200
Fire department's 119. Is it a fire or medical emergency?

00:28:14.200 --> 00:28:16.100
The landslide on the news? Yes, we're aware.

00:28:16.100 --> 00:28:18.160
Yes, we've heard of the landslide.

00:28:18.160 --> 00:28:20.980
It is already on our radar.

00:28:20.980 --> 00:28:24.150
People will be calling after seeing this on the news.

00:28:24.830 --> 00:28:27.170
Yokohama Fire Bureau, this is the SR Captain speaking.

00:28:27.170 --> 00:28:28.600
Go ahead, Captain.

00:28:28.600 --> 00:28:32.090
We'll arrive at District 3 in about 15 minutes, over.

00:28:32.090 --> 00:28:33.280
Copy that, Captain.

00:28:33.280 --> 00:28:38.260
The affected households are the Saejimas...

00:28:39.490 --> 00:28:41.460
Kiryus...

00:28:42.660 --> 00:28:44.680
Horiguchis...

00:28:47.050 --> 00:28:51.290
and Ishikuras? Thank you very much.

00:28:51.290 --> 00:28:52.890
We're checking now to see

00:28:52.890 --> 00:28:55.590
if any of them were in their homes.
[Ishikura]

00:28:55.590 --> 00:28:59.660
Sir, a rescue squad will be assisting them. Please evacuate.

00:28:59.660 --> 00:29:01.110
Yes, I am aware

00:29:01.110 --> 00:29:04.180
I must ensure everyone has evacuated.
[Saejima, Horiguchi, Kiryu, Ishikura]

00:29:04.180 --> 00:29:07.920
- I will call again if we need more assistance.
- Hatakeyama-san!

00:29:10.560 --> 00:29:12.340
Kaneshita?

00:29:13.670 --> 00:29:15.670
The Ishikuras...

00:29:17.370 --> 00:29:19.620
They're my in-laws, where my wife and son are.

00:29:25.100 --> 00:29:28.000
Fire department's 119. Is it a fire or medical emergency?

00:29:28.000 --> 00:29:31.150
A-An ambulance!

00:29:31.150 --> 00:29:33.900
My husband collapsed as soon as he came home!

00:29:33.900 --> 00:29:36.500
Please tell us where to send the ambulance, Ma'am.

00:29:36.500 --> 00:29:40.340
It's 16-7 Komyodai, Izumi Ward.

00:29:40.340 --> 00:29:42.300
We are the Mikamis.

00:29:42.300 --> 00:29:46.290
He didn't trip and fall. He collapsed in on himself,

00:29:46.290 --> 00:29:49.230
clutching his chest, and now he isn't moving!

00:29:49.230 --> 00:29:53.260
Is your husband conscious? Do you see him breathing?

00:29:53.260 --> 00:29:56.140
Dear? Dear!

00:29:56.140 --> 00:30:00.340
He's breathing, but I don't think he's conscious.

00:30:00.340 --> 00:30:02.600
He looks to be in incredible pain.

00:30:02.600 --> 00:30:04.840
He may be having angina or suffering a heart attack.

00:30:04.840 --> 00:30:07.090
Ma'am, does your husband have any chronic illnesses?

00:30:07.090 --> 00:30:12.450
No, but he has been complaining about his shoes feeling tighter.

00:30:13.830 --> 00:30:15.550
Dear?

00:30:15.550 --> 00:30:18.990
- Dear? Dear? Dear!
- What happened?

00:30:18.990 --> 00:30:23.870
He... He's... not breathing!

00:30:23.870 --> 00:30:27.200
Mikami-san. Mikami-san, please calm down.

00:30:27.200 --> 00:30:29.400
Fire department's 119. Is it a fire or medical emergency?

00:30:29.400 --> 00:30:33.320
- Mikami-san.
- My name is Ishikura.

00:30:33.320 --> 00:30:35.390
Yes. What seems to be the matter?

00:30:35.390 --> 00:30:38.070
My home was lost to a landslide.

00:30:38.070 --> 00:30:42.940
Is Kaneshita Mutsuo possibly there?

00:30:42.940 --> 00:30:46.170
- I am his mother-in-law.
- Mikami-san?

00:30:46.170 --> 00:30:47.130
- Hello?
- He's here.

00:30:47.130 --> 00:30:50.490
- Wake up, Dear!
- Mikami-san, if your husband has stopped breathing,

00:30:50.490 --> 00:30:54.930
we must perform CPR until the ambulance arrives.

00:30:55.810 --> 00:30:59.360
- Dear? Dear...
- Mikami-san, please.

00:30:59.360 --> 00:31:05.160
I'm terribly sorry, Ma'am, but Kaneshita is currently assisting another caller.

00:31:05.160 --> 00:31:08.470
No, I assumed. I apologize for asking.

00:31:08.470 --> 00:31:11.020
- He can't answer?
- No.

00:31:11.020 --> 00:31:13.180
He's currently helping someone else.

00:31:13.180 --> 00:31:15.630
Can't they have someone else take his call?

00:31:15.630 --> 00:31:17.770
- Mikami-san.
- Dear, don't.

00:31:17.770 --> 00:31:19.420
You're asking the impossible.

00:31:19.420 --> 00:31:21.890
Why is he busy now, of all times?

00:31:21.890 --> 00:31:23.710
I'm sorry about my husband.

00:31:23.710 --> 00:31:28.620
