00:31:51.740 --> 00:31:53.790
Yes. What do I do?

00:31:53.790 --> 00:31:55.280
First, lay your husband down, face-up.

00:31:55.280 --> 00:31:58.500
Please evacuate somewhere safe with your husband, Ma'am.

00:31:58.500 --> 00:32:01.800
We will. Thank you for answering when you must be busy.

00:32:01.800 --> 00:32:07.640
It's no worry at all. I will now end our call here.

00:32:07.640 --> 00:32:09.650
Is your husband lying face-up?

00:32:09.650 --> 00:32:13.090
One moment...

00:32:14.190 --> 00:32:17.500
Dear, were you always this skinny?

00:32:17.500 --> 00:32:22.000
He actually came home before the last train for once today.

00:32:24.040 --> 00:32:27.660
- He's lying down.
- I'll guide you through the rest.

00:32:27.660 --> 00:32:30.870
Next, kneel down next to your husband.

00:32:30.870 --> 00:32:33.180
- Okay.
- Now extend your arms,

00:32:33.180 --> 00:32:38.050
and you'll press down about 5 centimeters into your husband's chest.

00:32:38.050 --> 00:32:43.350
- Okay.
- Our rhythm with be one, two, three, four. Ready?

00:32:43.350 --> 00:32:47.580
One, two, three, four. One, two, three, four.

00:32:47.580 --> 00:32:49.720
One, two, three, four.

00:32:49.720 --> 00:32:51.130
One, two, three...

00:32:51.130 --> 00:32:58.790
Dispatchers are always the first to prevent a disaster.

00:32:59.510 --> 00:33:03.600
